\vspace{-8ex}                                                   %verringert Abstand zur Überschrift
\begin{abstract}                                                %Beginn des Abstracts
We measured the local equivalent dose rates in the laboratory and at different distances to a Cs-137 sample. The voltage dependent count rate of a Geiger counter was found to increase rapidly around a certain threshold voltage, above which it became nearly constant. The responsivity to $\gamma$-radiaton of the Geiger counter was measured to be about $0,5\%$. The half life of Ba-137m was found to be $T_\frac{1}{2}=(152,9\pm 1,2)\,\si\s$. We performed $\chi^2$-tests to analyze the distribution of decay events in an uranium trioxide coated tile for gate times $t_\text{gate}\in\{1\,\si\s;10\,\si\s\}$. The assumption that these follow a Poisson distribution could not be rejected at a $5\%$-significance level. The assumption that the Poisson distribution for $t_\text{gate}=10\,\si\s$ can be approximated by a normal distribution was rejected at the same significance level. 
\\ \\ 
\\ 
